Key Match Events: England beat Switzerland 5-3 on penalties to advance to the Euro 2024 semi-finals.
Breel Embolo scored for Switzerland in the 75th minute.
Bukayo Saka equalized for England with a stunning goal from outside the box five minutes later.
Trent Alexander Arnold scored the winning penalty for England.
Manuel Akanji missed a penalty for Switzerland, which was crucial in deciding the match outcome.
Jordan Pickford made a crucial save during the penalty shootout.
Post-Match Reflections: Bukayo Saka described the match as one of his best nights for England, expressing pride in the team's comeback and resilience.
Saka reflected on his redemption from missing a penalty in the Euro 2020 final, highlighting his faith and determination.
Boris Becker praised England's penalty shooting skills and expressed sympathy for Switzerland.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at the Dusseldorf Arena in Dusseldorf, Germany.
England will play the winner of the game between Netherlands and Turkey in the semi-finals.
Switzerland's dream of making it to their first-ever European Championships semi-final ended with the penalty shootout loss.
